3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bitget calculates ATOM/USDT funding rates using a composite index from major spot exchanges including Binance, OKX, and Bybit, with premium/discount components factored every minute. The 8-hour funding intervals provide more frequent arbitrage opportunities compared to daily funding systems. Funding payments are automatically debited or credited to perpetual positions at settlement times, with rates typically ranging from -0.375% to +0.375% for ATOM pairs."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","ATOM","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ATOM perpetuals exhibit significant funding rate volatility during Cosmos ecosystem developments, IBC updates, and staking reward adjustments. Bitget's ATOM/USDT pair benefits from the exchange's focus on altcoin derivatives and copy trading volume, creating unique arbitrage windows when retail sentiment diverges from institutional positioning."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ATOM/USDT funding rates on Bitget show distinct patterns around Cosmos Hub governance proposals and validator commission changes. Positive funding rates often spike during ATOM staking airdrops and IBC protocol upgrades, reaching 0.2-0.3% per 8-hour period. Negative rates typically occur during broader crypto market corrections when leveraged longs are liquidated. Weekend periods frequently show lower funding volatility due to reduced institutional activity, making these optimal times for stable arbitrage positioning."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Cross-exchange funding arbitrage between Bitget and Binance/OKX ATOM perpetuals can yield 0.5-2% monthly returns during high volatility periods. Bitget's copy trading ecosystem creates funding rate inefficiencies when popular traders take large directional positions in ATOM. Delta-neutral strategies work best by longing ATOM perpetuals when funding is deeply negative while shorting spot ATOM on lending platforms. The 8-hour funding frequency allows for three daily optimization opportunities compared to once-daily funding on some exchanges."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ATOM's moderate liquidity on Bitget means large arbitrage positions may face slippage during volatile periods, particularly around major Cosmos announcements. Funding rate calculations can be affected by extreme premium/discount scenarios when ATOM spot prices diverge significantly across exchanges. Bitget's newer derivative infrastructure may experience system issues during high volatility, potentially affecting funding payments or position liquidations. Cross-exchange arbitrage requires careful management of withdrawal limits and transfer times, especially during network congestion periods for Cosmos Hub."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"What are typical ATOM/USDT funding rates on Bitget?","answer":"ATOM/USDT funding rates on Bitget typically range from -0.1% to +0.15% per 8-hour period during normal market conditions. During high volatility or major Cosmos ecosystem events, rates can reach ±0.3% per period."},{"question":"How does Bitget's ATOM funding compare to other exchanges?","answer":"Bitget's 8-hour funding intervals provide more frequent arbitrage opportunities than Binance's daily funding. The exchange's copy trading volume can create funding inefficiencies, but liquidity is typically lower than tier-1 exchanges during extreme market conditions."},{"question":"What's the minimum position size for ATOM funding arbitrage on Bitget?","answer":"Effective ATOM funding arbitrage on Bitget typically requires minimum positions of $10,000+ to overcome the 0.02% maker fees and potential slippage. Smaller positions may not generate sufficient returns to justify the execution risks and capital requirements."},{"question":"When do ATOM funding payments occur on Bitget?","answer":"ATOM/USDT funding payments on Bitget occur every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC. Positions must be held at the exact settlement time to receive or pay the funding amount based on the calculated rate."}]}]
